  {
    "client_msg_id": "E19733DE-9685-4DC2-ABA0-341A6B8E1D59",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "My thinking along these lines tends away from talks and towards connecting people for potential collaboration/mentoring/friendship. My main beef with conferences is that they're a long way to travel to listen to dubiously good talks that I could listen to only the good ones of at home in my pajamas at 2x speed. I'm going to meet people, so why have any talks? Why not just facilitate productive introductions and let people talk to each other? ",
    "user": "U5TCAFTD3",
